blocks.name: expdioph
blocks.content: The exponential function is Diophantine. This result completes and encapsulates our development using Pell equation solution sequences and is sometimes regarded as Matiyasevich's theorem properly. (Contributed by Stefan O'Rear, 17-Oct-2014.)
blocks.origin:
thm expdioph(setvar s0) {
  |- wcel(crab(s0, co(cn0, cmap, co(nat1, cfz, nat3)), wceq(cfv(cv(s0), nat3), co(cfv(cv(s0), nat1), cexp, cfv(cv(s0), nat2)))), cfv(cdioph, nat3))
